<subSubSection lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1775,2017]" lastBlockId="50.[151,1437,150,213]" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1991,2017]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
I have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[559,660,1991,2017]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
, including the male genitalia, of 
<taxonomicName authority="(ZMHB)" baseAuthorityName="ZMHB" box="[1031,1342,1991,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radhakishunae">
<emphasis box="[1031,1232,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. radhakishunae</emphasis>
(ZMHB)
</taxonomicName>
, and the 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,150,176]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="(RBINS)" baseAuthorityName="RBINS" box="[295,527,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilio">
<emphasis box="[295,417,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">H. pumilio</emphasis>
(RBINS)
</taxonomicName>
(see figures in 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, P. D." box="[706,879,150,176]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="149 - 167" refId="ref50801" refString="Perkins, P. D. (2019 a) Type designations for Neotropical water beetles in the genus Hydrochus Leach, 1817. (Coleoptera: Hydrochidae). Zootaxa, 4701 (2), 149 - 167. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4701.2.2" type="journal article" year="2019">Perkins, 2019a</bibRefCitation>
), and conclude without doubt that they represent different species. The locality data of the specimen imaged, from Nova Teutonia, (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1154,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–29" captionStartId="66.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[171,1427,225,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-28@66.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURES 28–29. Habitus and male genitalia. 28. Hydrochus curvus n. sp., holotype 29. Hydrochus radhakishunae Makhan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5043312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5043312/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) is given above.
</paragraph>
